Sandra Rotman Chair in Social Work at the [[University of Toronto]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socialwork.utoronto.ca/about-us/endowed-chairs/#rotman|title=Endowed Chairs|last=|first=|date=|website=Factor-Inwentash Faculty of Social Work|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> which is ranked 18th among all universities globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/university-toronto|title=Times Higher Education, University of Toronto|last=|first=|date=|website=Times Higher Education|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Prior to his appointment as Dean in July, 2019 he was a Professor at the University of Chicago's School of Social of Social Service Administration for two decades and Director and Co-Director at the STI/HIV Intervention Network and the Chicago Center for HIV Elimination, also at the [[University of Chicago]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socialwork.utoronto.ca/profiles/dexter-voisin/|title=Dexter R. Voisin|last=|first=|date=|website=Factor-Inwentash Faculty of Social Work|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He is recognized as one of the most influential and cited Black scholars in premier schools of social work in North America.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Huggins-Hoyt, K. Y., Holosko, M. J., Briggs, H. E., & Barner, J. R.|first=|date=2015|title=Citation impact scores of top African American scholars in social work schools: The story behind the data.|url=https://eric.ed.gov/?id=EJ1048334|journal=Research on Social Work Practice|volume=25(1)|pages=164-170|via=}}</ref> His expertise and research findings have been frequently cited by numerous members of the international, national, and local media. He is the author of the book ''American the beautiful and violent: Black youth and neighborhood trauma in Chicago'', which is published by Columbia University Press<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cup.columbia.edu/book/america-the-beautiful-and-violent/9780231184410|title=Columbia University Press|last=|first=|date=|website=Columbia University Press|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n----[DV1]<nowiki>https://cup.columbia.edu/book/america-the-beautiful-and-violent/9780231184410</nowiki>\n<br />\n== Selected media coverage ==\nVoisin's expertise and research findings have been frequently cited by numerous members of the international, national, and local media:\n\n* \"Concerns about China\u2019s influence don\u2019t end at the WHO, experts say. They\u2019re calling for sweeping reviews of international bodies,\" Toronto Star, April 16, 2020<ref>{{Cite news|last=Nuttal, Jeremy; Chiu, Joanna|first=|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2020/04/14/concerns-about-chinas-influence-dont-end-at-the-who-experts-say-theyre-calling-for-sweeping-reviews-of-international-bodies.html|title=Concerns about China\u2019s influence don\u2019t end at the WHO, experts say. They\u2019re calling for sweeping reviews of international bodies|date=April 15, 2020|work=Toronto Star|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201cAmerica the beautiful tackles structural issues in Chicago,\u201d ''WTTW, PBS'', Chicago, January 29, 2020<ref>{{Cite news|last=Paddock|first=Blair|url=https://news.wttw.com/2020/01/29/america-beautiful-and-violent-tackles-structural-issues-chicago|title=\u2018America the Beautiful and Violent\u2019 Tackles Structural Issues in Chicago|date=January 29, 2020|work=WTTW, PBS|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201c'We all pay the cost' of city violence,\" ''Chicago Sun Times'', January 21, 2020<ref>{{Cite news|last=Steinberg|first=Neil|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/opinion/2020/1/21/21075332/chicago-violence-racial-repression-dexter-voisin-book|title=\u2018We all pay the cost\u2019 of city violence|date=January 21, 2020|work=Chicago Sun Times|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \"U of T\u2019s Dexter Voisin takes a deep dive into the issues that drive neighborhood violence in Chicago and beyond,\" ''U of T News'', August 14, 2019<ref>{{Cite news|last=Levine|first=Romi|url=https://www.utoronto.ca/news/u-t-s-dexter-voisin-takes-deep-dive-issues-drive-neighbourhood-violence-chicago-and-beyond|title=U of T\u2019s Dexter Voisin takes a deep dive into the issues that drive neighbourhood violence in Chicago and beyond|date=August 14, 2019|work=U of T News|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \"Dexter Voisin to become new dean at Factor-Inwentish School of Social Work,\" ''U of T News'', May 17, 2019<ref>{{Cite news|last=Blackwell|first=Richard|url=https://www.utoronto.ca/news/dexter-voisin-become-new-dean-u-t-s-factor-inwentash-faculty-social-work?utm_source=Bulletin+Brief&utm_campaign=70c6ee2531-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2018_06_13_COPY_03&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_66bc4ba557-70c6ee2531-109977679|title=Dexter Voisin to become new dean of U of T\u2019s Factor-Inwentash Faculty of Social Work|date=May 17, 2019|work=U of T News|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \"Confab examines STIs and HIV among youth,\" ''Windy City Times'', November 11, 2013<ref>{{Cite news|last=Clifton|first=Derrick|url=http://www.windycitymediagroup.com/lgbt/Confab-examines-STIs-and-HIV-among-youth/45147.html|title=Confab examines STIs and HIV among youth|date=November 12, 2013|work=Windy City Times|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \"A Chicago reporter questions news about the city's violence,\" ''StarTribune'', March 16, 2013<ref>{{Cite news|last=Moore|first=Natalie Y.|url=https://www.startribune.com/a-chicago-reporter-questions-news-about-the-city-s-violence/198610651/?refer=y|title=A Chicago reporter questions news about the city's violence|date=March 16, 2013|work=StarTribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201cImpact of street violence on Chicago youth,\" ''Chicago Tonight'', ''PBS'', February 28, 2013<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://news.wttw.com/2013/02/28/impact-street-violence-chicago-youth|title=Impact of Street Violence on Chicago Youth|date=February 28, 2013|work=WTTW (PBS)|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201cTeens exposed to gun violence face tough road,\" ''NPR'', March 26, 2011<ref>{{Cite news|last=Corley|first=Cheryl|url=https://www.npr.org/2011/03/26/132078175/teens-exposed-to-gun-violence-face-tough-road|title=Teens Exposed To Gun Violence Face Tough Road|date=March 26, 2011|work=NPR, Special Series|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* In Chicago, stopping crime before it happens,\" ''NPR'', March 25, 2011<ref>{{Cite news|last=Corley|first=Cheryl|url=https://www.npr.org/2011/03/25/132633966/chicago-youth-program-aims-to-decrease-violence|title=In Chicago, Stopping Crime Before It Happens|date=March 25, 2011|work=NPR, Special Series|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201cProfessor\u2019s goal: Separate HIV facts from fiction,\" ''Chicago Tribune'', December 28, 2009<ref>{{Cite news|last=Trice|first=Donna Turner|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-2009-12-28-0912280043-story.html|title=Professor's goal: Separate HIV facts from fiction|date=December 28, 2009|work=Chicago Tribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201c36 Chicago area students killed sets record,\" ''Washington Times'', May 13, 2009<ref>{{Cite news|last=Billups|first=Andrea|url=https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/may/13/record-36-students-killed-this-school-year-across-/|title=36 Chicago area students killed sets record|date=May 13, 2009|work=The Washington Times|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* \u201cDeadly Lessons: 24 Hours in Chicago,\" ''Anderson Cooper 360 Degrees, CNN'', June 3, 2007<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www-news.uchicago.edu/citations/07/070603.voisin-cnn.html#dv|title=Deadly Lessons: 24 Hours in Chicago|date=June 3, 2007|work=Anderson Coo[er 360 Degrees, CNN|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n\n\n{{US-academic-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Dalannd", "label": "safe", "comment": "formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dexter_R._Voisin"}
{"title_page": "Max Reinthaler", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Max Reinthaler\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Maximilian Reinthaler<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/augsburg/sport/Der-FCA-Nachwuchs-und-der-steinige-Weg-in-die-Bundesliga-id31648642.html|title=Der FCA-Nachwuchs und der steinige Weg in die Bundesliga|last=Allgemeine|first=Augsburger|work=Augsburger Allgemeine|access-date=2017-11-20|language=de}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|3|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Bolzano]], Italy\n| height = 1.93m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]]\n| clubnumber = 14\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132009\n| youthclubs1 = [[F.C. S\u00fcdtirol|S\u00fcdtirol]]\n| youthyears2 = 2009\u20132013\n| youthclubs2 = [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2 = [[TSV Gersthofen]]\n| caps2 = 12\n| goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2014\n| clubs3 = [[Rydaholms GoIF]]\n| caps3 = \n| goals3 = \n| years4 = 2014\u20132018\n| clubs4 = [[FC Augsburg II]]\n| caps4 = 68\n| goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]]\n| caps5 = 20\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs6 = [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock II]]\n| caps6 = 7\n| goals6 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| medaltemplates = \n| club-update = 9 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}'''Maximilian Reinthaler''' (born 22 March 1995) is an Italian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]]<ref name=\":0\" /> for [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nReinthaler was born in [[Bolzano]], Italy. He made his debut on 6 December 2012 with [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Udinese v Liverpool|url=http://espnfc.com/us/en/commentary/355859/commentary.html?soccernet=true&cc=5901|accessdate=6 December 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Max Reinthaler \u00bb Club matches\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler \u00bb Club matches |url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/max-reinthaler/2/ |publisher=World Football |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> Although being part of the [[Serie A]] squad on several occasions, he never earned a cap.\n\nIn Summer 2013, Reinthaler had trials with both [[SC Freiburg]] and [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]. However, due to compensation demands by [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]], no agreement was reached. In order to evade Udinese's claims, Reinthaler regained amateur status by joining German sixth tier club [[TSV Gersthofen]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Reinthaler wechselt von Udinese in die bayrische Provinz|trans-title=Max Reinthaler transfers from Udinese to Bavarian countryside|language=German|date=12 September 2013|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/max-reinthaler-wechselt-von-udinese-in-die-bayrische-provinz.html}}</ref> While playing for Gersthofen he scored five goals in twelve appearances.\n\nFrom April to July 2014, Reinthaler enjoyed a short spell at Swedish fifth tier club [[Rydaholms GoIF]]. In an interview he claimed that the offer he had received by Rydaholm had been too lucrative.<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Reinthaler: \"Die vergangenen Monate haben mich gepr\u00e4gt\"|trans-title=Max Reinthaler: \"The last couple of months have shaped me\"|language=German|date=28 July 2014|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/max-reinthaler-die-vergangenen-monate-haben-mich-gepraegt.html}}</ref>\n\n===FC Augsburg===\nIn July 2014, it was announced that Reinthaler had signed for German side [[FC Augsburg]] on a four-year contract, running until 2018. He was assigned to the second team, playing in the [[Regionalliga Bayern]], but will occasionally train with the first team.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|title=F\u00fcr Max Reinthaler \u00f6ffnen sich die Tore der Bundesliga|trans-title=Open gates to the Bundesliga for Max Reinthaler|language=German|date=22 July 2014|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/fuer-max-reinthaler-oeffnen-sich-die-tore-der-bundesliga.html}}</ref> He also takes part in the first team's training camp and first team's friendly fixtures.<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Reinthaler startet mit Augsburgs Profis ins Trainingslager|trans-title=Max Reinthaler takes off to Augsburg first team's training camp|language=German|date=27 July 2014|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/max-reinthaler-startet-mit-augsburgs-profis-ins-trainingslager.html}}</ref> He made 24 appearances in the [[2014\u201315 Regionalliga|2014\u201315 season]],<ref name=\"2014\u201315 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2014-15/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref> 17 appearances in the [[2015\u201316 Regionalliga|2015\u201316 season]],<ref name=\"2015\u201316 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2015-16/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> nine appearances in the [[2016\u201317 Regionalliga|2016\u201317 season]],<ref name=\"2016\u201317 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2016-17/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref> and 18 appearances in the [[2017\u201318 Regionalliga|2017\u201318 season]].<ref name=\"2017\u201318 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2017-18/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n===Hansa Rostock===\nHe signed for [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]] on 18 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Der n\u00e4chste Neue: Rostock verpflichtet Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/rlby/725844/artikel_der-naechste-neue_rostock-verpflichtet-reinthaler.html |website=kicker.de |date= 18 June 2018 |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref> He made his club debut on 18 August 2018 when he came on as a substitute in the 89th minute in the first round of the German Cup against [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Soukou sorgt f\u00fcr eine magische Hansa-Nacht |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2018-19/1/4214408/spielbericht_hansa-rostock-3_vfb-stuttgart-11.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=9 October 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis hometown is [[Bolzano]] in [[South Tyrol]], Italy. His [[first language]] is [[German language|German]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|matches played on 9 March 2020.}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"National Cup\">Includes appearances in the [[DFB-Pokal]] and Landespokal MV.</ref>!!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<ref name=\"Europa League\" group=\"lower-alpha\">Appearances in the [[UEFA Europa League]].</ref>!!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!rowspan=\"2\"|{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]||[[2012\u201313 Udinese Calcio season|2012\u201313]]||[[Serie A]]||0||0||0||0||1||0||1||0||<ref name=\"Max Reinth