ate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Udinese Calcio players]]\n[[Category:FC Augsburg II players]]\n[[Category:FC Augsburg players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Hansa Rostock players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:3. Liga players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Max Reinthaler\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Maximilian Reinthaler<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/augsburg/sport/Der-FCA-Nachwuchs-und-der-steinige-Weg-in-die-Bundesliga-id31648642.html|title=Der FCA-Nachwuchs und der steinige Weg in die Bundesliga|last=Allgemeine|first=Augsburger|work=Augsburger Allgemeine|access-date=2017-11-20|language=de}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|3|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Bolzano]], Italy\n| height = 1.93m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]]\n| clubnumber = 14\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132009\n| youthclubs1 = [[F.C. S\u00fcdtirol|S\u00fcdtirol]]\n| youthyears2 = 2009\u20132013\n| youthclubs2 = [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2 = [[TSV Gersthofen]]\n| caps2 = 12\n| goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2014\n| clubs3 = [[Rydaholms GoIF]]\n| caps3 = \n| goals3 = \n| years4 = 2014\u20132018\n| clubs4 = [[FC Augsburg II]]\n| caps4 = 68\n| goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]]\n| caps5 = 20\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs6 = [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock II]]\n| caps6 = 7\n| goals6 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| medaltemplates = \n| club-update = 9 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}'''Maximilian Reinthaler''' (born 22 March 1995) is an Italian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]]<ref name=\":0\" /> for [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nReinthaler was born in [[Bolzano]], Italy. He made his debut on 6 December 2012 with [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Udinese v Liverpool|url=http://espnfc.com/us/en/commentary/355859/commentary.html?soccernet=true&cc=5901|accessdate=6 December 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Max Reinthaler \u00bb Club matches\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler \u00bb Club matches |url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/max-reinthaler/2/ |publisher=World Football |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> Although being part of the [[Serie A]] squad on several occasions, he never earned a cap.\n\nIn Summer 2013, Reinthaler had trials with both [[SC Freiburg]] and [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]. However, due to compensation demands by [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]], no agreement was reached. In order to evade Udinese's claims, Reinthaler regained amateur status by joining German sixth tier club [[TSV Gersthofen]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Reinthaler wechselt von Udinese in die bayrische Provinz|trans-title=Max Reinthaler transfers from Udinese to Bavarian countryside|language=German|date=12 September 2013|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/max-reinthaler-wechselt-von-udinese-in-die-bayrische-provinz.html}}</ref> While playing for Gersthofen he scored five goals in twelve appearances.\n\nFrom April to July 2014, Reinthaler enjoyed a short spell at Swedish fifth tier club [[Rydaholms GoIF]]. In an interview he claimed that the offer he had received by Rydaholm had been too lucrative.<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Reinthaler: \"Die vergangenen Monate haben mich gepr\u00e4gt\"|trans-title=Max Reinthaler: \"The last couple of months have shaped me\"|language=German|date=28 July 2014|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/max-reinthaler-die-vergangenen-monate-haben-mich-gepraegt.html}}</ref>\n\n===FC Augsburg===\nIn July 2014, it was announced that Reinthaler had signed for German side [[FC Augsburg]] on a four-year contract, running until 2018. He was assigned to the second team, playing in the [[Regionalliga Bayern]], but will occasionally train with the first team.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|title=F\u00fcr Max Reinthaler \u00f6ffnen sich die Tore der Bundesliga|trans-title=Open gates to the Bundesliga for Max Reinthaler|language=German|date=22 July 2014|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/fuer-max-reinthaler-oeffnen-sich-die-tore-der-bundesliga.html}}</ref> He also takes part in the first team's training camp and first team's friendly fixtures.<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Reinthaler startet mit Augsburgs Profis ins Trainingslager|trans-title=Max Reinthaler takes off to Augsburg first team's trainings camp|language=German|date=27 July 2014|accessdate=4 August 2014|publisher=sportnews.bz|url=http://www.sportnews.bz/de/fussball/news-detail/news/max-reinthaler-startet-mit-augsburgs-profis-ins-trainingslager.html}}</ref> He made 24 appearances in the [[2014\u201315 Regionalliga|2014\u201315 season]],<ref name=\"2014\u201315 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2014-15/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref> 17 appearances in the [[2015\u201316 Regionalliga|2015\u201316 season]],<ref name=\"2015\u201316 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2015-16/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> nine appearances in the [[2016\u201317 Regionalliga|2016\u201317 season]],<ref name=\"2016\u201317 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2016-17/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref> and 18 appearances in the [[2017\u201318 Regionalliga|2017\u201318 season]].<ref name=\"2017\u201318 season\">{{cite web |title=Max Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/vereine/2017-18/75509/vereinsspieler_reinthaler-max.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n===Hansa Rostock===\nHe signed for [[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]] on 18 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Der n\u00e4chste Neue: Rostock verpflichtet Reinthaler |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/rlby/725844/artikel_der-naechste-neue_rostock-verpflichtet-reinthaler.html |website=kicker.de |date= 18 June 2018 |publisher=kicker |accessdate=2 July 2018 |language=German}}</ref> He made his club debut on 18 August 2018 when he came on as a substitute in the 89th minute in the first round of the German Cup against [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Soukou sorgt f\u00fcr eine magische Hansa-Nacht |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2018-19/1/4214408/spielbericht_hansa-rostock-3_vfb-stuttgart-11.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=9 October 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis hometown is [[Bolzano]] in [[South Tyrol]], Italy. His [[first language]] is [[German language|German]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|matches played on 9 March 2020.}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"National Cup\">Includes appearances in the [[DFB-Pokal]] and Landespokal MV.</ref>!!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<ref name=\"Europa League\" group=\"lower-alpha\">Appearances in the [[UEFA Europa League]].</ref>!!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!rowspan=\"2\"|{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|